#. type: Content of: <guide><abstract>
#: en/genkernel.xml:27
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This guide intends to provide a reference of all the functions provided by\n"
"genkernel.\n"
msgstr "このガイドは、genkernelにより提供される全機能のリファレンスを提供することを意図しています。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:39 en/genkernel.xml:870
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "はじめに"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Rationale"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For users who don't want to manually compile their kernels, genkernel is a tool\n"
"to automate this process. It can help you create a kernel image akin to those\n"
"available on Gentoo Installation CDs, which are designed to auto-detect the\n"
"hardware configuration of your system. Some users may also be interested in\n"
"using genkernel for hardware requiring initialization and a working kernel\n"
"before the system starts up.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "Target Audience"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:60
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you are either uncertain about how to compile a kernel, or are just\n"
"unfamiliar with your hardware configuration, genkernel is a very handy tool.\n"
"It is designed to take the pain out of the kernel compiling process, and\n"
"supports most hardware by default.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:67
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"However, if you know what drivers are required by your system, you may be able\n"
"to further reduce the time taken to compile the kernel. This is possible since\n"
"you can direct genkernel to only build drivers relevant to your hardware.\n"
"Oftentimes, the number of drivers required by your system will be fewer\n"
"(implying a shorter kernel compilation time) than the default configuration\n"
"provides.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:78
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Installing genkernel"
msgstr "genkernelの取得"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:82
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To obtain genkernel, run <c>emerge genkernel</c> from the command line. Consult\n"
"<c>genkernel --help</c> for help on how to use the version of genkernel\n"
"installed on your system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:92
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Working with genkernel"
msgstr "genkernelの移植"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:94
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "How to use genkernel"
msgstr "genkernelの移植"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Although there are several ways to run genkernel, the least-intrusive approach\n"
"is provided by <c>genkernel all</c>. Here, a generic configuration which works\n"
"well for most systems is used. As was mentioned earlier, this approach is not\n"
"without drawbacks; most of the modules created are useless to the average user\n"
"and may increase compile time. Below is an illustration of a more efficient\n"
"approach, achieved by passing certain flags to genkernel as root:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:106
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Running genkernel (with flags)"
msgstr "genkernelの実行"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "# <i>genkernel --splash --no-install --no-clean --menuconfig all</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:111
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The above operation causes genkernel to create a framebuffer splash-enabled\n"
"kernel (<c>--splash</c>) that will have to be manually installed\n"
"(<c>--no-install</c>). While preparing the kernel source tree, genkernel will\n"
"refrain from cleaning out any preexisting object files present in the source\n"
"tree (<c>--no-clean</c>). A menu-driven kernel configuration utility will be\n"
"displayed that allows the user to select which modules will be built for the\n"
"system (<c>--menuconfig</c>).\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"There are other flags which alter the result provided by genkernel. For\n"
"instance, replacing <c>--no-install</c> with the <c>--install</c> flag allows\n"
"genkernel to automatically install the new kernel in the <path>/boot</path>\n"
"directory, and will create symlinks for you if <c>--symlink</c> is specified.\n"
"Using the <c>--mountboot</c> flag allows genkernel to mount your\n"
"<path>/boot</path> partition automatically, if necessary.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:130
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Remember, genkernel is designed to make kernel compilation easy and\n"
"stress-free. For this reason, genkernel features several flags to ease the\n"
"kernel compilation effort. For example, there are flags to help with kernel\n"
"configuration, while others affect the actual compilation. Some flags even help\n"
"debug the compilation process. For those interested in further optimization,\n"
"there are flags that affect kernel assembling, packaging and even kernel\n"
"initialization.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The rest of this chapter examines the functionality of various flags,\n"
"configuration variables, and actions available for genkernel. For a more\n"
"complete list, please refer to <c>man genkernel</c> and the comments in\n"
"<path>/etc/genkernel.conf</path>. Some of the flags have variants which\n"
"perform a converse operation. The converse variants carry the <b><c>no-</c></b>\n"
"prefix, and their effects are enclosed within the square brackets, [].\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:151
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Configuration Flags"
msgstr "カーネル設定ファイル"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:155
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The configuration flags listed below exist to help you decide what features\n"
"should be enabled or disabled in the kernel prior to compilation. You can even\n"
"choose whether or not the configuration file created in the process should be\n"
"saved. The following are the primary configuration flags:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:163
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>menuconfig</b>: Activates <e>[or deactivates]</e> the\n"
"    <c>make menuconfig</c> command (which invokes an interactive, menu-based\n"
"    kernel configuration utility), before building the kernel.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--gconfig</b>: Provides a kernel configuration utility which depends on\n"
"    the GTK+ libraries. The advantage of this option is that most users find it\n"
"    easier and clearer to configure the kernel using this tool, since it relies\n"
"    on the X-windowing system. The disadvantage of this option is that you\n"
"    <b>need</b> the X-windowing system to use it, so it will not work on the\n"
"    command line.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:176
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--xconfig</b>: Provides a kernel configuration utility which depends on\n"
"    the QT libraries. The advantage of this option is that most users find it\n"
"    easier and clearer to configure the kernel using this tool, since it relies\n"
"    on the X-windowing system. The disadvantage of this option is that you\n"
"    <b>need</b> the X-windowing system to use it, so it will not work on the\n"
"    command line.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:184
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>save-config</b>: Saves <e>[or does not save]</e> the kernel\n"
"    configuration to a file in the <path>/etc/kernels/</path> directory for\n"
"    later use.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>menuconfig</b>: This runs <e>or does not run</e> the kernel \n"
"    これは、<c>make oldconfig</c>が実行された後、\n"
"    あなたのカーネルをビルドする前にメニューベースのカーネル設定を実行するか<e>あるいは実行しません</e>。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid "Compilation Flags"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following flags usually take effect during the actual compilation:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:202
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--kerneldir=<path>/path/to/sources/</path></b>: Specifies an alternative\n"
"    kernel source location, rather than the default\n"
"    <path>/usr/src/linux/</path> location.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--kerneldir=<path>/path/to/sources</path></b>:\n"
"    これは、デフォルトの場所である<path>/usr/src/linux</path>の代わりに代替のカーネルソースの場所を指定します。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:207
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--kernel-config=<path>/path/to/config-file</path></b>: Specifies what\n"
"    alternative kernel configuration will be used, rather than the default\n"
"    <path>/path/to/sources/.config</path> file.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--kernel-config=<path>/path/to/config-file</path></b>:\n"
"    これは、使用される代替のカーネル設定を指定します。\n"
"    デフォルトで使用される持続性のない<path>/path/to/sources/.config</path>の代わりに使用されます。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:212
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--module-prefix=<path>/path/to/prefix-directory/</path></b>: Specifies a\n"
"    prefix to the directory where kernel modules will be installed (default\n"
"    path is the <path>/lib/modules/</path> directory.)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--kerneldir=<path>/path/to/sources</path></b>:\n"
"    これは、デフォルトの場所である<path>/usr/src/linux</path>の代わりに代替のカーネルソースの場所を指定します。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:220
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>clean</b>: Activates <e>[or deactivates]</e> the <c>make\n"
"    clean</c> command before compiling your kernel. The <c>make clean</c>\n"
"    command removes all object files and dependencies from the kernel's source\n"
"    tree.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>clean</b>:\n"
"    これは、あなたのカーネルを構築する前に<c>make clean</c>を実行するか<e>あるいは実行しません。</e>\n"
"    これは、全てのオブジェクトファイルと依存関係が削除されます。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:226
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>mrproper</b>: Activates <e>[or deactivates]</e> the <c>make\n"
"    mrproper</c> command before kernel compilation. Like the <c>make clean</c>\n"
"    command, <c>make mrproper</c> removes all object files and dependencies\n"
"    from the kernel's source tree. However, any previous configuration files\n"
"    (in <path>/path/to/sources/.config</path> or\n"
"    <path>/path/to/sources/.config.old</path>) will <b>also</b> be purged from\n"
"    the kernel's source tree.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:235
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--oldconfig</b>: Issues the <c>make oldconfig</c> command, which\n"
"    attempts to collect configuration information for the system's architecture\n"
"    from a generic script in <path>/usr/share/genkernel/</path>.  This is a\n"
"    non-interactive process; no user input is entertained. Also, if\n"
"    <c>--oldconfig</c> is used in conjunction with <c>--clean</c>, the latter\n"
"    flag is negated, resulting in the activation of the <c>--no-clean</c> flag.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:246
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--callback=\"<c>echo hello</c>\"</b>: Calls the specified arguments\n"
"    (<c>echo hello</c>, in this case) after the kernel and the relevant modules\n"
"    have been built, but before building the initrd image. This may be useful\n"
"    if you want to install external modules in the initrd image by emerging the\n"
"    relevant item(s) with the callback feature, and then redefining a genkernel\n"
"    module group.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--callback=\"echo Hello\"</b>:\n"
"    このルーチンはカーネルと関連モジュールがビルドされた後に指定された引数を呼びます。\n"
"    しかし、initrdが構築される前です。\n"
"    これは、コールバックを使用することによりgenkernelモジュールグループを再定義して、\n"
"    関連項目をemergeする事によってinitrdに外部モジュールをインストールしたいと思う場合に有用です。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:257
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>install</b>: Activates <e>[or deactivates]</e> the <c>make\n"
"    install</c> command, which installs your new kernel image, configuration\n"
"    file, initrd image and system map onto your mounted boot partition. Any\n"
"    compiled modules will be installed as well.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:263
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--no-ramdisk-modules</b>: Refrains from copying any modules to the\n"
"    genkernel-created initrd image. This flag is an exception to the rule about\n"
"    the <c>no-</c> prefix; omission of this prefix creates an invalid genkernel\n"
"    flag.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:269
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--all-ramdisk-modules</b>: Copies all available modules to the\n"
"    genkernel-created initrd image.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"  <b>--no-initrdmodules</b>: これは、genkernelが作成するinitrdにモジュールを全くコピーしません。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:273
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--genzimage</b>: Creates the initrd image, prior to the kernel image.\n"
"    (This hack currently applies only to PPC Pegasos systems.)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:281
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
