#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:320
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--utils-as=<c>someAssembler</c></b>: Specifies the assembler employed\n"
"    during the compilation of support utilities.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--utils-as=<c>someAssembler</c></b>: これはサポートユーティリティを構築する時に使われるアセンブラを指定します。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:324
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--utils-make=<c>someMake</c></b>: Specifies an alternative to the <e>GNU\n"
"    make</e> utility employed during the compilation of support utilities.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    <b>--utils-make=<c>someMake</c></b>: これはサポートユーティリティを構築する時に使われるGNU makeの代替を指定します。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--makeopts=<c>-jX</c></b>: Specifies the number of concurrent threads\n"
"    that the make utility can implement while the kernel (and utilities) are\n"
"    being compiled. The variable <b>'X'</b> is a number obtained by adding one\n"
"    (1) to the number of CPUs used by the system. So, for a system with one\n"
"    CPU, the appropriate flag is <c>-j2</c>; a system with two CPUs will use\n"
"    the <c>-j3</c> flag, and so on. <e>(A system with one processor that\n"
"    supports Hyper-Threading&trade; (HT) Technology can use the\n"
"    </e><c>-j3</c><e> flag, provided Symmetric Multi-Processing (SMP) support is\n"
"    enabled in the kernel.)</e>\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:346
#, no-wrap
msgid "Debugging Flags"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:350
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The use of debugging flags during the kernel compilation process controls the\n"
"amount of information reported, as well as the presentation of said data.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:356
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--loglevel=<c>verblevel</c></b>: Controls the level of verbosity for\n"
"    information provided by genkernel. The variable <c>verblevel</c> is an\n"
"    integer between 0 and 5. The level '0' represents minimal output, while '5'\n"
"    provides as much information as possible about genkernel's activities\n"
"    during the kernel compilation process.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:363
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--logfile=<path>/path/to/outputfile</path></b>: Ignores the value set\n"
"    by the <c>--loglevel</c> argument, and sends <b>all</b> debugging data\n"
"    produced by genkernel to the specified output file, which is located at\n"
"    <path>/var/log/genkernel.log</path> by default.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:369
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--no-color</b>: Activates <e>[or deactivates]</e> colored output of\n"
"    debugging information (reported by genkernel) using escape sequences.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:378
#, no-wrap
msgid "Initialization Flags"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:382
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The flags here are used to create certain effects during system startup. Some\n"
"of these flags are primarily for aesthetics, while others may be essential for\n"
"enabling certain features on the system.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:389
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--<c>no-</c>splash</b>: Activates <e>[or deactivates]</e> support for\n"
"    <uri link=\"http://fbsplash.berlios.de/wiki/doku.php\">framebuffer\n"
"    splash</uri> support in the genkernel-built initrd image. To override the\n"
"    default theme used by fbsplash, use <b>--splash=<c>PreferredTheme</c></b>\n"
"    (where <c>PreferredTheme</c> is the title of one of the directories inside\n"
"    the <path>/etc/splash/</path> directory.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:397
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--splash-res=<c>PreferredResolution</c></b>: This flag allows you to\n"
"    select which splash screen resolutions will be supported in the initrd\n"
"    during the start-up of the system. This is useful for two reasons: First,\n"
"    you are able to select only the splash screen resolution(s) relevant to your\n"
"    system. Second, you avoid the unnecessary increase in the disk space\n"
"    required by initrd (since the initrd does not have to support resolutions\n"
"    that are irrelevant for your system configuration.) However, you may want to\n"
"    omit this flag if the kernel is being compiled for an Installation CD; this\n"
"    allows splash support for all possible resolutions.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:408
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--do-keymap-auto</b>: Force keymap selection during the boot sequence.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:411
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--lvm</b>: Includes support for storage using via <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://sources.redhat.com/lvm2/\">Logical Volume Management</uri>\n"
"    (LVM2) from <e>static</e> binaries, if available to the system. Relevant\n"
"    (static) LVM2 binaries are compiled if they are unavailable. Be sure to\n"
"    install the lvm2 package on your system with <c>emerge lvm2</c> before\n"
"    enabling this flag, and review the <uri link=\"/doc/en/lvm2.xml\">Gentoo LVM2\n"
"    Installation</uri> guide.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:420
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--dmraid</b>: Includes support for <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://people.redhat.com/~heinzm/sw/dmraid/readme\">DMRAID</uri>; the\n"
"    utility which creates RAID mappings using the kernel device-mapper\n"
"    subsystem. DMRAID discovers, activates, deactivates and displays properties\n"
"    of software RAID sets (ATARAID, for example) and contained DOS partitions.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:427
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--luks</b>: Includes support for <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://luks.endorphin.org/\">Linux Unified Key Setup</uri> or LUKS.\n"
"    This will allow you to use a device encrypted by LUKS which contains the\n"
"    root filesystem. On the bootloader, you then set that encrypted device as\n"
"    the value of crypt_root (and real_root shall be the unencrypted device LUKS\n"
"    creates).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:435
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--disklabel</b>: Adds support for disk label and UUID support to your\n"
"    initrd.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:439
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--iscsi</b>: Adds support for iSCSI to your initrd.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:442
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--multipath</b>: Adds support for <uri\n"
"    link=\"/doc/en/multipath.xml\">Multipath</uri> to your initrd.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:446
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--linuxrc=/path/to/your/linuxrc</b>: Specifies a user-created\n"
"    <e>linuxrc</e> &mdash; a script that is initialized during the start-up\n"
"    stage of the kernel, prior to the actual boot process. (A default linuxrc\n"
"    script should be in the <path>/usr/share/genkernel/</path> directory.) This\n"
"    script allows you to boot into a small, modularized kernel and load the\n"
"    drivers that are needed (as modules) by the system.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:454
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--cachedir=/path/to/alt/dir/</b>: Overrides the default cache location\n"
"    used while compiling the kernel.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:458
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--tempdir=/path/to/new/tempdir/</b>: Specifies the location of the\n"
"    temporary directory used by genkernel while compiling the kernel.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:462
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--unionfs</b>: Includes support for the <uri\n"
"    link=\"http://www.fsl.cs.sunysb.edu/project-unionfs.html\">Unification File\n"
"    System</uri> in the initrd image.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:471
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Miscellaneous Flags"
msgstr "genkernelの様々なフラグ"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:475
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The assortment of flags listed below are supported by genkernel, but do not fit\n"
"neatly into any of the other categories:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:481
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--mountboot</b>: Detects whether or not the <path>/boot/</path>\n"
"    directory needs to be mounted on a separate partition. It will check\n"
"    <path>/etc/fstab</path> script for instructions on how to mount the boot\n"
"    partition on a file system (if needed).\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:487
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>--kernname=<c>NickName</c></b>: Allows you to modify the name of the\n"
"    kernel and initrd images in the <path>/boot/</path> directory, so that the\n"
"    images produced are kernel-<c>NickName</c>-version and\n"
"    initramfs-<c>NickName</c>-version.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:497
#, no-wrap
msgid "Possible Actions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:501
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"An action tells genkernel what to build. Currently, the following actions are\n"
"supported:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:507
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <c>all</c>: Builds all stages &mdash; the initrd, kernel image and modules.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:509
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "<c>bzImage</c>: Only builds the kernel image"
msgstr "\"kernel\"モード: これは、カーネルイメージをビルドするのみです。"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:510
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "<c>kernel</c>: Only builds the kernel image and modules"
msgstr "\"kernel\"モード: これは、カーネルイメージをビルドするのみです。"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:511
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>initramfs</c>: Only builds the initramfs/ramdisk image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:512
#, no-wrap
msgid "<c>ramdisk</c>: Only builds the initramfs/ramdisk image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:516
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The first action, <c>all</c>, is recommended for most users since it builds the\n"
"stages required for a functional kernel. Remember, an <e>action</e> simply\n"
"tells genkernel what to <e>build</e>, not <e>install</e>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:524
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Bootloader Configuration"
msgstr "カーネル設定ファイル"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:528
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To set up genkernel to work with your bootloader, three or four changes should\n"
"be applied to the bootloader's configuration file:\n"
msgstr ""
"ブートローダで動くようにgenkernelをセットアップするには、\n"
"ブートローダの設定に3つか4つの変更が必要です。\n"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:534
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Add <c>real_root=/dev/sda3</c>, for example, to the kernel parameters\n"
"    passed to the kernel image, if <path>/dev/sda3</path> contains your root\n"
"    partition.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    例えば<path>/dev/hda3</path>にルートパーティションが含まれているならば、\n"
"    <c>real_root=/dev/hda3</c>をカーネルイメージに渡されるカーネルパラメータに加えてください。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:539
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    If you are using splash, add a suitable mode line such as <c>vga=0x317</c>\n"
"    to the parameters passed to the kernel and also add <c>splash=verbose</c> or\n"
"    <c>splash=silent</c> depending on the verboseness you require from your\n"
"    bootloader.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    もしブートスプラッシュを使いたいならば、\n"
"    <c>vga=0x317</c>といった適したモードラインをカーネルイメージに渡されるカーネルパラメータに加えてください。\n"
"    そして、あなたがブートスプラッシュに冗長さを要求するかどうかによる<c>splash=verbose</c>または<c>splash=silent</c>も加えてください。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:545
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Add the initrd information as required by the bootloader. Consult the <uri\n"
"    link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=10\">Bootloader\n"
"    Configuration Chapter</uri> of the Gentoo Handbook for details on how to\n"
"    make your bootloader initrd-aware.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"    ブートローダがどの様にそれを必要とするかによってinitrdを加えてください:\n"
"    あなたがお使いのブートローダではどの様にするかの詳細は、\n"
"    <uri link=\"/doc/en/handbook/handbook-x86.xml?part=1&amp;chap=10\">Gentoo  Handbook</uri>を参照してください。\n"
"  "

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:557
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Configuration Options"
msgstr "設定ファイル"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:559
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Editing /etc/genkernel.conf"
msgstr "genkernelの取得"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:563
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Passing flags to genkernel from the command line can be cumbersome, especially\n"
"if you have about a dozen flags:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:567
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running genkernel (overloaded with flags)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:568
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>genkernel --loglevel=5 --no-color --no-mrproper --clean --splash \\\n"
"--kerneldir=/path/to/alternate/kernel/sources --install --menuconfig \\\n"
"--kernel-config=/path/to/preferred/configfile --save-config --mountboot all</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:574
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Fortunately, there is a configuration file where most of the basic options can\n"
"be set (or changed) as necessary: <path>/etc/genkernel.conf</path>. What follows\n"
"is a rundown of the more relevant options:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:581
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>MENUCONFIG=<c>[yes|no]</c></b>: This option is equivalent to the\n"
"    <c>--menuconfig</c> flag used by genkernel, which in turn uses the <c>make\n"
"    menuconfig</c> command to invoke a command-line based kernel configuration\n"
"    utility. To invoke the utility automatically during kernel configuration\n"
"    via this script, set this option to 'yes' here; otherwise, choose 'no'.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:588
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>CLEAN=<c>[yes|no]</c></b>: Setting this option to 'yes' is equivalent to\n"
"    the <c>--clean</c> flag used by genkernel, and invokes the <c>make\n"
"    clean</c> command to remove all object files and dependencies from the\n"
"    kernel's source tree. Setting this option to 'no' creates a cascade effect\n"
"    &#8212; it is equivalent to genkernel's <c>--no-clean</c> flag, which\n"
"    disables the <c>make clean</c> command and implies genkernel's\n"
"    <c>--no-mrproper</c> flag &mdash; essentially nullifying the <c>make\n"
"    mrproper</c> command.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:598
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>MRPROPER=<c>[yes|no]</c></b>: Setting this option to 'yes' is equivalent\n"
"    to <c>--mrproper</c> flag used by genkernel, and invokes the <c>make\n"
"    mrproper</c> command, which purges the kernel source tree of any\n"
"    configuration files. Selecting 'no' here is equivalent to genkernel's\n"
"    <c>--no-mrproper</c> flag, which disables the <c>make mrproper</c> command.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:605
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>MOUNTBOOT=<c>[yes|no]</c></b>: Setting this option to 'yes' is\n"
"    equivalent to the <c>--mountboot</c> flag, and automatically mounts the\n"
"    <path>/boot/</path> directory (if needed) at compile time. If the\n"
"    <path>/boot/</path> directory is on a separate partition, consider enabling\n"
"    this option; it will make for one less (essential) step to remember later.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:612
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>SAVE_CONFIG=<c>[yes|no]</c></b>: After configuring the kernel, the\n"
"    selected options are stored as <path>.config</path> in the kernel source\n"
"    tree. This script may be overwritten during the next kernel compilation, or\n"
"    even purged from the kernel source tree. Choosing 'yes' here is equivalent\n"
"    to the <c>--save-config</c> flag, and stores all options selected during\n"
"    kernel configuration as a script in the <path>/etc/kernels/</path>\n"
"    directory. Choosing 'no' preserves the <e>status quo</e>.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:621
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>USECOLOR=<c>[yes|no]</c></b>: Setting this option to 'yes' is equivalent\n"
"    to the <c>--color</c> flag, which colors genkernel's output to ease\n"
"    debugging (when needed.)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ul><li>
#: en/genkernel.xml:626
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>LOGLEVEL=<c>[0|1|2|3|4|5]</c></b>: This option is for adjusting the\n"
"    verbosity of the output produced by genkernel &mdash; setting this option to\n"
"    '0' with <c>--loglevel=0</c> will suppress all output produced by\n"
"    genkernel; setting this option to '5' with <c>--loglevel=5</c> provides\n"
"    the user with all output produced by genkernel.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/genkernel.xml:635
#, no-wrap
msgid "More options are described in <path>/etc/genkernel.conf</path>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:639
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"By choosing the appropriate options in <path>/etc/genkernel.conf</path>, you\n"
"can halve the number of flags passed to genkernel from the command line:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:643
#, no-wrap
msgid "Running genkernel (with flags), after employing genkernel.conf"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:644
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# <i>genkernel --splash --kerneldir=/path/to/alternate/kernel/sources \\\n"
"--kernel-config=/path/to/preferred/configfile --install all</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:649
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Identical results are obtained from both approaches, but the latter has most of\n"
"the options stored in a script that can be modified at a later date.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:658
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Network-Booting with genkernel"
msgstr "genkernelの取得"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:660
#, no-wrap
msgid "Network Booting from an Installation CD"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:664
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The genkernel utility can build kernel and initrd images that provide support\n"
"for network booting, or <e>netboot</e>ing. With any luck, you should be able\n"
"to netboot any recent computer into the environment provided by the\n"
"Installation CD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:671
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The magic lies in genkernel's linuxrc script: it will try to <e>netmount</e>\n"
"the Installation CD using NFS. From there, <e>the init scripts</e> of the\n"
"Installation CD can take over, as if the CD was present locally.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:679
#, no-wrap
msgid "Building Kernel and Initrd Images with Support for Netbooting"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:683
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To enable support for netbooting, include the following options while\n"
"configuring the kernel:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><warn>
#: en/genkernel.xml:688
#, no-wrap
msgid "Support for netbooting with genkernel is experimental and may contain bugs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:692
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"First, the kernel image must include the drivers for your Network Interface\n"
"Cards (NIC). Normally, drivers for such devices will be compiled as modules.\n"
"However, it is essential (for netbooting) that you have such drivers compiled\n"
"directly into the kernel image and <b>not</b> as modules.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:698
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring a 2.6.x series kernel to support your NIC driver"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:699
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Device Drivers --->\n"
"   Networking Support --->\n"
"      Ethernet (10 or 100Mbit)  --->\n"
"         [*] Ethernet (10 or 100Mbit)\n"
"         &lt;*&gt;   the driver for your network card\n"
"<comment>(Be sure to select &lt;*&gt; and not &lt;M&gt;)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:708
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Secondly, we suggest that you enable <c>IP: kernel level autoconfiguration</c>\n"
"and the <c>IP: DHCP support</c> options. This avoids an unnecessary layer of\n"
"complexity since the IP address and the NFS path to the Installation CD can be\n"
"configured on a DHCP server. Of course, this means the kernel command line\n"
"will remain constant for any machine &mdash; which is very important for\n"
"<e>etherbooting</e>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:716
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring a 2.6.x series kernel to support DHCP"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:717
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Device Drivers --->\n"
"   Networking Support --->\n"
"      Networking options\n"
"         [*] TCP/IP networking--->\n"
"         [*]   IP: kernel level autoconfiguration\n"
"         [*]     IP: DHCP support\n"
"<comment>(These options tell the kernel to send a DHCP request at bootup.)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:727
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Additionally, you should enable SquashFS because most modern Gentoo\n"
"Installation CDs require it. Support for SquashFS is not included with the\n"
"generic kernel source tree. To enable SquashFS, apply the necessary patches to\n"
"the generic kernel source or install <c>gentoo-sources</c>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:733
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configuring the kernel to support SquashFS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:734
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"File systems--->\n"
"   Miscellaneous filesystems --->\n"
"      [*] SquashFS 2.X - Squashed file system support\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:740
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Once the compilation process is completed, create a compressed <e>tarball</e>\n"
"(tar.gz) that contains the kernel's modules. This step is only necessary if\n"
"your kernel version does not match the kernel image version on the Installation\n"
"CD.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:746
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a compressed tarball containing the kernel modules"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:747
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Create a tar.gz containing all the modules)</comment>\n"
"# <i>cd /</i>\n"
"# <i>tar -cf /tmp/modules-X.Y.Z.tar.gz /lib/modules/X.Y.Z/</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:753
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Depending on your network boot mechanism, you will need to do some of the\n"
"following steps:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:757
#, no-wrap
msgid "Creating a boot image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:758
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(Create an etherboot image)</comment>\n"
"# <i>emerge mknbi</i>\n"
"# <i>cd /boot</i>\n"
"# <i>mkelf-linux -params=\"root=/dev/ram0 init=/linuxrc ip=dhcp\" kernel... initrd... > etherboot.img</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Create a OpenBoot / SPARC64 TFTP image)</comment>\n"
"# <i>emerge sparc-utils</i>\n"
"# <i>cd /boot</i>\n"
"# <i>elftoaout kernel... -o kernel.aout</i>\n"
"# <i>piggyback64 kernel.aout System.map-... initrd-...</i>\n"
"# <i>mv kernel.aout openboot.img</i> <comment>(This is the boot image)</comment>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(PXE does not need any more steps, the kernel and initrd can be used as is)</comment>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:774
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Finally, copy this kernel to your TFTP server. The details are\n"
"architecture-dependent and are beyond the scope of this guide. Please refer to\n"
"the documentation for your platform.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:782
#, no-wrap
msgid "NFS Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:786
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"To setup a NFS share that contains the Installation CD, use the loop device to\n"
"mount the ISO image and then copy the contents of the CD into the NFS share. As\n"
"a nice extra, genkernel's initrd scripts will extract all tar.gz files located\n"
"in the <path>/nfs/livecd/add/</path> directory. All you have to do here is copy\n"
"the <c>modules-X.Y.Z.tar.gz</c> archive to the <path>/nfs/livecd/add/</path>\n"
"directory.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:794
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparing the NFS share"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:795
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment>(This assumes that /nfs/livecd is an exported NFS share)</comment>\n"
"# <i>mount /tmp/gentoo-livecd.iso /mnt/cdrom -o loop</i>\n"
"# <i>cp -p /mnt/cdrom /nfs/livecd</i>\n"
"# <i>umount /mnt/cdrom</i>\n"
"\n"
"<comment>(Copy the modules.tar.gz into /add)</comment>\n"
"# <i>mkdir /nfs/livecd/add</i>\n"
"# <i>cp /tmp/modules-X.Y.Z.tar.gz /nfs/livecd/add</i>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:808
#, no-wrap
msgid "DHCP Setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:812
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The netboot images will ask your DHCP server for an IP as well as a root-path\n"
"parameter. Both can be specified per host using a MAC address to identify\n"
"machines:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:817
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sample client dhcpd.conf setup"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:818
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"...\n"
"\n"
"host netbootableMachine {\n"
"         hardware ethernet 11:22:33:44:55:66;\n"
"         fixed-address 192.168.1.10;\n"
"         option root-path \"192.168.1.2:/nfs/livecd\";\n"
"}\n"
"<comment># Here, 192.168.1.2 is the NFS server\n"
"# While 192.168.1.10 will be the IP address of the netbooted machine</comment>\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:833 en/genkernel.xml:844
#, no-wrap
msgid "Netbooting Instructions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:837
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Netbooting itself is again very platform-specific. The important part is to\n"
"specify the <c>ip=dhcp</c> and <c>init=/linuxrc</c> parameters on the kernel\n"
"command line, as this will bring up the network interface and tell the initrd\n"
"scripts to mount the Installation CD via NFS. Here are some platform-specific\n"
"tips:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:845
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment># Etherboot - insert the etherboot disk into the drive and reboot\n"
"# The kernel command line was specified when the image was constructed</comment>\n"
"\n"
"<comment># Sparc64 - Hit Stop-A at the boot prompt</comment>\n"
"ok boot net ip=dhcp init=/linuxrc\n"
"\n"
"<comment># PXE - Setup pxelinux (part of syslinux),\n"
"then create a pxelinux.cfg/default along the lines of:</comment>\n"
"\n"
"DEFAULT gentoo\n"
"TIMEOUT 40\n"
"PROMPT 1\n"
"\n"
"LABEL gentoo\n"
"    KERNEL kernel-X.Y.Z\n"
"    APPEND initrd=initrd-X.Y.Z root=/dev/ram0 init=/linuxrc ip=dhcp\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:868
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
msgid "Booting a genkernel initramfs"
msgstr "genkernelの取得"

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:874
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you installed an initramfs with genkernel, you should definitely take a look\n"
"at the various boot options that you can (or need to) define in your bootloader\n"
"configuration. The most common ones are added to this guide for your reference.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:882
#, no-wrap
msgid "Loading LVM or software-RAID"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:886
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If your system uses LVM or software-RAID, you undoubtedly have built the\n"
"initramfs using the <c>--lvm</c> and <c>--mdadm</c> options (didn't you).\n"
"However, you should not forget to enable support during boot as well. This can\n"
"be done using the <c>dolvm</c> and <c>domdadm</c> options.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:892
#, no-wrap
msgid "Enabling LVM and/or MDADM support"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:893
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment># Example for GRUB 1.x</comment>\n"
"title Gentoo Linux\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /vmlinuz root=/dev/md3 <i>dolvm domdadm</i>\n"
"initrd /initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-3.4.3\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'caption' of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:903 en/genkernel.xml:912
#, no-wrap
msgid "Booting in single-user mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/genkernel.xml:907
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If for some reason boot-up fails, you might be able to rescue your system by\n"
"booting in the single-user mode. This will only load the really necessary\n"
"services and then drop you to a rescue (root) shell.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><pre>
#: en/genkernel.xml:913
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<comment># Example for GRUB 1.x</comment>\n"
"title Gentoo Linux\n"
"root (hd0,0)\n"
"kernel /vmlinuz root=/dev/md3 <i>init_opts=S</i>\n"
"initrd /initramfs-genkernel-x86_64-3.4.3\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><title>
#: en/genkernel.xml:925
#, no-wrap
msgid "Conclusion"
msgstr ""

